partial_descriptions: Model A almost always deploys a terse, mechanical “Step 1, Step 2…” outline, jumping straight into formulas or computations with little narrative framing. Model B, by contrast, tends to weave a more conversational narrative around each solution—often restating the problem, unpacking why each step follows, and sometimes even checking special cases or giving extra context. Structurally, A sticks rigidly to brief, numbered instructions, while B mixes numbered steps with fuller paragraphs and explicit justifications. Qualitatively, A feels brisk and procedural, whereas B reads more like a guided tutorial with richer explanations.

final_description: Across all batches, Model A adopts a sparse, mechanical outline—usually a numbered list of procedural steps with minimal narrative or justification—often jumping straight to formulas or computations and sometimes truncating context or checks. Model B, in contrast, weaves its solutions into more discursive, conversational expositions: restating the problem, providing high-level overviews, explaining rationale, recalling relevant theorems, and verifying intermediate results. Structurally, A favors uniform “Step 1, Step 2…” bullet points, whereas B mixes prose with headings or subheadings to produce a more cohesive tutorial-style write-up. Qualitatively, A feels brisk and utilitarian, while B reads as a self-contained guided walkthrough with fuller explanations.
